    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="160" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <head>No. 160.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">West</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-01-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 10,
                                1884</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to previous correspondence,
                            I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your note of the 2d
                            instant, in regard to the application of the Canadian Telegraph Company
                            to land a cable in Washington Territory, and to inform you that the
                            matter is receiving the consideration of this Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
